Encountered in the wild:
```Modelica
model A
    parameter Boolean flag;
end A;

model B
    Real x;
    A a(flag=x);
end B;
```
Two things are wrong, but are not caught (but _can_ lead to an error e.g. when using MXFunction caching):
1. Setting the default value of a _parameter_ with a state. Default values of parameters should probably only be allowed to be constants and parameters. Same goes for inputs (if, as we do, default values are allowed for those as well).
2. Setting a Boolean with a Real.
